                                3cHELP SYSOP0
 
                             3g--- General ---0
 
    Citadel allows someone at remote to have full power over Citadel.  The following describes which sysop commands are available.
 
                       3g--- File linked messages --0
 
  3b.E*0   -- Enter Filelinked Public Message.
  3b.M*E0  -- Enter Exclusive Filelinked Message.
  3b.EL*M0 -- Enter Limited Access Filelinked Message.
 
    The Sysop only can enter Filelinked messages. Either at console or remote.  You must specifly the entire DOS path including drive.  No wildcard file names are allowed.
 
                       3g--- Sysop menu commands ---0
 
    The sysop menu can be accessed by remote by hitting ".S", it can also be accessed by hitting "F6" at console.
 
  "3bA0" -- Abort   Aborts sysop functions.
  "3bD0" -- Date    Changes system date and time.
  "3bE0" -- Enter/update EXTERNAL.CIT and GRPDATA.CIT files
  "3bF0" -- Aide Function    Allows sysop access to aide functions.
 
  "3bG0" -- Group special functions. The following are available.
 
     "3bK0" -- Group special: Kill group
     "3bN0" -- Group special: New group
     "3bG0" -- Group special: Global group membership.
     "3bU0" -- Group special: Global User group membership.
     "3bR0" -- Group special: Rename group
 
  "3bH0" -- Hallway special functions. The following are available.
  
     "3bF0" -- Hallway special: Force
     "3bG0" -- Hallway special: Global hallway.
     "3bK0" -- Hallway special: Kill
     "3bL0" -- Hallway special: List
     "3bN0" -- Hallway special: New
     "3bR0" -- Hallway special: Rename
 
  "3bK0"  -- Kill account.    Kills a userlog entry.
  "3bM0"  -- Mass delete.     Kills all messages from a user.
  "3bN0"  -- Newuser Verify   Scrolls through all the unverified users, and
                           asks you if you want to verifiy them.  If you do
                           not verify them, GremCit will offer to kill the
                           account.
  
  "3bR0" -- Reset file info.    Clears unused entries from fileinfo.cit.
  "3bS0" -- Show user.          Displays a user's configuration.
  "3bU0" -- Userlog edit.       Changes a user's setup.
  "3bV0" -- View help file.     Shows this text file.
  "3bX0" -- Exit to Ms-dos.     This is the proper way of exiting Citadel.
  "3bZ0" -- Zap empty rooms.    Deletes empty rooms.
 
  "3b!0" -- Shell escape  Allows person at console to drop into dos while
                       GremCit is running.  Type 'Exit' to return to Citadel.
                       Only works in console mode.
 
  "3@0" -- Super Shell Escape  Allows someone at console to drop into dos
                             while GremCit is running. Type 'Exit' to return
                             to GremCit.  Saves parts of GremCit to disk, and
                             frees more memory for the shell. Only works in
                             console mode.
 
  "3b#0" -- Read by message #   Displays message according to # if it is
                             viewable.
 
  "3b*0" -- Unlink with wildcards. Allows the sysop to erase files and use
                                full UNIX style wildcards.
 
                           3g--- Console keys ---0
 
    These keys work only on the local console.
 
   3bAlt-P0               Toggle printer on/off.
   3bAlt-T0               Toggle problem user bit of user logged in.
   3bAlt-X0               Exit to DOS. Same as "X".
   3bAlt-F60              Toggles current logged in user's Aide status.
   3cShift-F60            Toggles currently logged in user's SysOp status.
   3bAlt-B0               Turns the PsYcHo cHiCkEn eFfEcT on or off.
   3bAlt-C0               Pulls a user into Chat mode like F8.
   3bAlt-D0               Debug mode - shows all command processes
   3bAlt-Z0               Hangs Up.  Sleeping Call again :-)
   3ePgUp0                Add 5 min time to user on line
   3ePgDn0                Subtract 5 min time from user on line
   3eF10                  Dump Caller from system (hangs up)
   3eF20                  ReInitialize modem
   3eF30                  System Request - beeps you when system is free
   3eF40                  Toggles 'Screen saver'
   3eF50                  Toggles Modem/Console mode
   3eF60                  Access Sysop menu
   3eF70                  Toggles Sound (page noise)
   3eF80                  Pulls caller into chat
   3eF90                  Toggles Chat mode
   3eF100                 Toggles double status line
